  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are some Indian Fast-fashion Brands?",
  "response": "India has seen the rise of several homegrown fast-fashion brands that cater to the growing demand for trendy, affordable, and quick-to-market clothing. Here are some notable Indian fast-fashion brands:\n\n1. **Zivame**: While primarily known for its lingerie, Zivame has expanded into other fast-fashion categories, offering stylish and affordable options for women.\n\n2. **Myntra**: A leading online fashion retailer in India, Myntra offers a wide range of fast-fashion products from various brands, including its private labels like Roadster, Dressberry, and HRX.\n\n3. **Ajio**: Owned by Reliance Retail, Ajio is an online fashion platform that offers trendy and affordable clothing, accessories, and footwear for men, women, and kids.\n\n4. **Vero Moda**: Although it\u2019s a Danish brand, Vero Moda has a strong presence in India and is known for its Western-style fast-fashion offerings for women.\n\n5. **Forever 21**: While originally an American brand, Forever 21 has a significant presence in India, offering trendy and affordable fast-fashion items for young men and women.\n\n6. **Bewakoof**: Known for its quirky and youthful designs, Bewakoof offers a range of casual wear, including t-shirts, hoodies, and accessories, at affordable prices.\n\n7. **FabIndia**: While FabIndia is not a traditional fast-fashion brand, it has adapted to the market by offering a mix of traditional and contemporary styles that are produced quickly to meet consumer demand.\n\n8. **Max Fashion**: Part of the Landmark Group, Max Fashion offers a wide range of affordable clothing and accessories for men, women, and children, focusing on the latest trends.\n\n9. **Pantaloons**: A well-known retail chain in India, Pantaloons offers fast-fashion products under its own brand as well as other labels, catering to a wide range of customers.\n\n10. **Global Desi**: Known for its vibrant and ethnic-inspired designs, Global Desi offers a range of clothing and accessories that blend traditional Indian styles with contemporary trends.\n\nThese brands have carved out a niche in the Indian market by offering stylish, affordable, and quickly produced fashion items that appeal to the younger, trend-conscious consumer base.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
